docker start and attach later to go inside running container.
or 
docker run directly


always add and use names to container, otherwise have to use container id.
 
 
 can run container with --rm to execute one time tasks.

docker commit to save/create new image from existing container


use docker save to save images into tar file to make it portable.

use docker load to make image from tar file and then use docker run.


use docker run -v local_path:container_path to map local directory to container.
This way, we can keep the configuration locally and change it as needed dynamically.(For example httpd.conf)
